latestPosts.caption:
The reason I’m sharing this is that maybe someone will feel motivated by it.🫶🏻✨

So, basically, I am a lifestyle blogger. About a week ago, I received a call from an employee at L’Oréal’s research center. They were looking for someone with knowledge in skincare and haircare who is also a content creator. They asked if I could share some insights with their clients. But before confirming, they conducted a mock interview, which I was completely unaware of. I didn’t expect to get selected at all.🙈♥️

After the interview, I got a call saying I was selected. I was really nervous because I had to speak in a group interview with 2-3 other content creators, and I was one of them. And guess what? I told myself, “No matter what, I’ll share the knowledge I have and won’t let my nerves get the better of me. I won’t worry about what others think.😮‍💨✨

Plus, all the participants were Americans, including L’Oréal’s clients. Despite that, I managed to give the interview, which is a huge achievement for me.🌻💯

And the best part? This happened on my birthday, so I’m feeling extremely grateful, happy, and blessed.🫶🏻🧿

Thank you, Universe!🌻🌍

P.S. There were a few restrictions, which is why I couldn’t shoot.
